qas.question: Who is the mayor of Oklahoma City?
When was Mick Cornett first elected?

context: The City of Oklahoma City has operated under a council-manager form of city government since 1927. <a0_0>Mick Cornett<a0_0/> serves as Mayor, having first been elected in <a1_0>2004<a1_0/>, and re-elected in 2006, 2010, and 2014. Eight councilpersons represent each of the eight wards of Oklahoma City. City Manager <a2_0>Jim Couch<a2_0/> was appointed in late 2000. Couch previously served as assistant city manager, Metropolitan Area Projects Plan (MAPS) director and utilities director prior to his service as city manager.
